NDHU, Shoufeng

Event Description:

This activity is suitable for the following types of people: 1. Want to participate in Hult Prize but don't know what it really is ->There will be Hult Prize crew to help solve your questions on the day 2. Want to communicate with international students but have no channels ->The students in the International Team will be very enthusiastic to communicate with you 3. Get in touch with this kind of information, broaden your horizons, and develop the ability to think independently We welcome everyone to join us in the event!

Event Details

Chinese Info Seminar

+ Add to Calendar

Sep 23, 2020

7:00 PM

Event Description:

Why should you join Hult Prize? ?What you can gain through Hult Prize? 1. English Speaking Ability Although this competition is mainly in English (e.g. proposal writing, presentation material, and pitch), don't be discouraged by this, just team up with a person who’s good in English and you're set! This is also a good opportunity for you to train yourself! For those who are already good in English, this is definitely your place to shine! 2. Interesting Résumé Hult Prize is known as “Nobel Prize for students”, just by competing you’ll get the valuable #HultPrizeCertificate, which would catch eyes for your résumé. 3. Entrepreneurship Spirit Hult Prize’s goal is to “solve the world's toughest issues through the creation of for-good, for- profit businesses”, letting the participants to learn how to think and solve problems, to start from the bottom to the top, to let the impossible be possible! 4. Expand Your Views We’ll hold a series of “FREE workshops”, inviting speakers and professionals from different fields to share their experience, letting you accumulate the knowledge about entrepreneurship! Moreover, you’ll pay close attention to social problems and connect with the international world through these events! 5. Brainstorming Here you’ll engage with people from different departments and areas, get inspired with diverse ideas and views, break free from your circle! Interested?? If you want to know more, do come to our info seminars!

Event Details

English Matching Forum

+ Add to Calendar

Oct 19, 2020

6:30 PM

Event Description:

What is SDGs?? SDGs, short for Sustainable Development Goals, are the goals of the United Nations, which covers 3 important aspects: society, economy, and environment. Consisting of 17 main goals and 169 targets, the agenda started from 2016 and it seeks to achieve economic growth, society development and environmental protection by 2030.? The SDGs board game simply put is the game version of the real goals, players are divided into groups to play the roles of different businesses and figure out how to solve social issues by distributing the recourses owned. The game involves various social issues, hoping that once the game ends, the players could reflect on the result of every decision, and to realize what the most important thing in their heart is.? We also welcome those who are merely curious about the game! To let participants get to know each other through the SDGs board game and World Cafe. To explain what SDGs are, and how it relates to Hult Prize and the challenge.

Event Details

Beach Cleanup

+ Add to Calendar

Oct 24, 2020

9:00 AM

Event Description:

It seems impossible to pick up all the trash in the ocean…… Beach cleanup has been conducted in Taiwan for years, but has the environment really got better? According to Ocean Conservation Administration, from 2017 until 2020, there were up to 7000 beach cleanups, with a total of 300k people contributing, getting rid of more than 5 mil. kgs of ocean trash. Don't underestimate your power, one's contribution will make a huge difference Join us for the first beach cleanup by Hult Prize at NDHU. We will discuss how to minimize the problem of ocean waste through the 3Rs. Explain where the ocean waste in Taiwan come from ( tourists, fishing industry, and even foreign countries!) Explain how the plastic in the ocean affects our food system Enjoy a #zerowaste picnic by the ocean. Turn “Junk“ into “Food”, to promote #leavenotrace when we enjoy food at the beach. Visit the local fishery and fishing village to see how they make fishing nets, understand the Fixed Net Fishery, and interview fishermen . Discuss and reflect on different issues through the Six Thinking Hats model .
